The rise in obesity among Chinese city dwellers is alarming, with 70 million affected due to improved living standards.
Surveys in Shanghai and Beijing reveal high obesity rates, especially in males and certain age groups.
In Britain, unhealthy behaviors like heavy drinking and smoking are hindering efforts for a healthier nation.
Kuwait faces similar challenges, with hypnotherapy showing promise in treating obesity.
Globally, diabetes cases are set to double by 2025, driven by poor diets and sedentary lifestyles.
Urgent action is needed to address these escalating health concerns.
